          "contributor_id": "111492867744596190274",
          "user_review_count": 8,
          "user_photo_count": 7,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXC03CmqUmiIi3KRuqUA7Z753Zj2enyBDTua-HrvoPBcOzGgVNDRQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "\ud83e\uddb7\ud83e\udea5Dr. VanMeter is truly amazing at what he does. From the very beginning, he prioritized my overall health, not just the dental work. Because of my unstable blood pressure, he took the extra step to refer me to my cardiologist before administering anesthesia. That level of care and precaution meant everything to me, and I\u2019m so grateful for it. He made sure I had all the necessary medications and explained the proper methods to heal safely. His approach was gentle, kind, and highly professional, and his work speaks for itself.\n\nI have a serious phobia of dentists, and Dr. VanMeter completely calmed me down. His gentle hands and reassuring presence made a world of difference. As much as I\u2019d love to gatekeep him, other patients truly deserve to experience the care and compassion he provides.\n\nA huge shoutout to the incredible staff as well. D and Gen are wonderful assistants, so kind and supportive throughout the entire process. And I absolutely cannot forget Dacyia, the biller. She is honestly the main reason I ended up in this dental office. She was sweet, patient, and made me feel safe and understood from the start. This entire team is exceptional, and I\u2019m beyond thankful for the care I received \ud83d\udc99\ud83e\uddb7\ud83d\ude0a",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21aTFdIaFVUVEJSTTNwRk1VbHhiM0l5YzNoMlQwRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x7ae2db26e54b7056!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOmZLWHhUTTBRM3pFMUlxb3Iyc3h2T0E%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "4 months ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2026-02-04T19:20:26+00:00"
